Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan’s family are attending the Save SA gathering against state capture in Pretoria on Wednesday‚ and a letter he sent to the assembly was received by thunderous applause. In the letter‚ Gordhan said he was humbled by the support he had received. He described himself as a son of the ANC and reiterated former president Nelson Mandela’s words — "there is still a long walk". The minister himself was not in attendance but his letter was read out by a bishop at the St Alban’s church cathedral. ANC veterans in attendance included Mavuso Msimang and Cheryl Carolus as well as party Gauteng chairman Paul Mashatile. The national anthem was sung by Freshlyground lead singer Zolani Mahola. 